                        <div class="sing">
                            <div class="sing_date">January 9, 2013<span class="sing_by"> BY joed</span></div>
                            <div class="sing_title">A Quicker Way to Navigate Through SIDEARM</div>
                            <div class="sing_content"><p>We hope everyone enjoyed the Holiday season and had a chance to take some time off to spend with friends and family. As each of you get back into the swing of things, we wanted to pass along some additions we made to the software during the winter break.</p>
<p><strong>Quick Nav</strong></p>
<p>At the top of the SIDEARM Menu, there is now a search icon which will expand when hovered over or by typing ‘Control+Q’ on your keyboard. This is your Quick Nav search bar that will allow you to easily jump to different areas in SIDEARM.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/quick_nav_1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-268" src="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/quick_nav_1.png" alt="" width="284" height="73" /></a></p>
<p>Here, you can type in a section or action and you will be presented with options. Say you want to add a Roster, you can choose to type ‘Roster’ and then click to that section, or you can be more specific and type the exact wording ‘Add Roster’ and then select that option.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/quick_nav_3.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-267" src="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/quick_nav_3.png" alt="" width="283" height="75" /></a></p>
<p>To make it even easier, you can use the arrow keys on your keyboard to choose which option you want and then hit enter, or you can use your mouse.</p>
<p>This feature should save some time from having to scroll up and down the menu and will also help find sections that may seem hard to find. You will see this referenced more often in future posts that pertain to finding sections on the site.</p>
<p><strong>Schedule Filters</strong></p>
<p>For those who are using the “advanced” schedule format, we have added the option for users to filter between home, away and neutral games. Clicking one of those three options at the top of the schedule will “hide” those games allowing the user to filter to only seeing home or only away or only neutral games.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/schedule_filters.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-265" src="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/schedule_filters.png" alt="" width="899" height="320" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Batch Opponent Lookup Tab</strong></p>
<p>One item in schedules that has gotten a lot of attention lately is the ‘Batch Opponent Lookup’ area. This is used for linking logos in schedules, matching up team codes so you can submit schedules to the NCAA and also will be used for a new feature coming out later this month. So to make this page easier to access, we have added it as a tab option when in the schedule admin area. Now you can click on ‘Opponent Lookup’ to be brought to that section on each schedule.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/batch_opponent.png_tab.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-264" src="http://blog.sidearmsports.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/batch_opponent.png_tab.png" alt="" width="895" height="291" /></a></p>
<p>That concludes our software additions over the winter break. We would like to thank all the schools who have participated in testing out some of these and other new features that we have coming out on the horizon. Your assistance is vital to what we do and we thank you for your time and patience.</p>
